# musclemap-model — Project Overview

## What this project does
Takes a **text description of a motion** and outputs **muscle activations** — float32 [T, 80], values in [0,1].
Wraps a frozen MotionGPT backbone (T5 + VQ-VAE) with a trainable parallel activation head.

## Key architectural facts
- MotionGPT backbone lives at `vendor/MotionGPT/` — NEVER modify files under vendor/
- Trainable: ActivationHead (src/head.py) + LoRA adapters on T5 decoder (Stage 2 only)
- Loss: BCEWithLogitsLoss (primary) + temporal smoothness. NOT MSE.
- DDP wraps ONLY ActivationHead, NOT the full MotionGPT model
- Output: raw logits inside training; Sigmoid applied only at inference

## Dataset (Project 1 output)
- Root: config/train.yaml -> data.dataset_root
- Per sample: activations.npy [T,80] float32, smplx_322.npy [T,322] float32, semantic_label.txt
- Shared: muscle_names.json — 80 muscles, Rajagopal2016
- fps=30, median T≈172, max T=483, ~12000 sequences

## Commands
- Setup:   bash scripts/setup.sh
- Train:   torchrun --nproc_per_node=2 scripts/train.py --config config/train.yaml
- Eval:    python scripts/evaluate.py --config config/train.yaml --split test
- App:     python app/app.py
- CLI:     python app/demo.py --text "a person walks" --output-npy out.npy
- Tests:   pytest -q
- Lint:    ruff check src/ scripts/ app/ tests/

## Constraints
- Python 3.10, conda env musclemap-model
- PyTorch 2.x, bf16 on 2x NVIDIA A30 24GB
- No opensim imports — reads .npy files from Project 1 only
- matplotlib.use('Agg') BEFORE any plt import (headless server)
- Cross-platform paths (no hardcoded /home/ or C:\\)
